26 June 2014The Ministerial Enquiry on Lwandle evictions led by Advocate Denzel Potgieter SC will on Monday, 30 June 2014, brief members of the media on the progress and operations of the enquiry.Minister of Human Settlements Lindiwe Sisulu established the Ministerial Enquiry on 4 June 2014 to look into the recent evictions effected by the South African National Roads Agency Limited (SANRAL) on the members of the informal settlement of Nomzamo (Lwandle), located in the City of Cape Town in the Western Cape.Details of the media briefing are as follows:Date: Monday, 30 June 2014 Time: 10h00 Place: Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, National Parliament, Cape Town.Enquiries: Vusi Tshose (Spokesperson for the Enquiry) Cell: 083 581 5265.Issued by: Department of Communications on behalf of Ministerial enquiry on Lwandle